Directions: Travel to Carr Powerhouse area of park. Cross bridge and go 0.3 miles to gravel road on right. Sign says "Boulder Creek Falls Trail." Gravel road will fork, take right. Sign will say "Road Dead Ends in 1.5 Miles." Go 1.0 miles and park. From pullouts (multiple ones are here), walk up handline/fuel break on NW side of road for 608m (Note: this was measured with a tape, but does not account for all small bends.). You should end up on a small bench below a high point. There is a group of 3 oaks (QUKE) - there are 3 stems and the 4th one is cut - with tree tag #223 on the stem farthest from the line. Oaks are approximately 4m from line. From this tagged tree, go 82 degrees for 49m to Q3. Plot runs downhill from here.
